.sh NAME
thresh \*- GRINNELL interactive thresholding
.sh SYNOPSIS
.bd thresh
[b [w]]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.it
Thresh
allows the
user to interactively select a threshold
for an image
using the TRACK ball unit.
The horizontal screen position of cursor 1
is used to select the current threshold. By moving this cursor to the left
or right the threshold will move down or up the grayscale
respectively.
.s3
If present, the first parameter gives the black value instead of the
default 0.  The optional second parameter gives the white value instead
of the default 4095.
